    # game/areas/ruinedshelter.rpy:289
    old "It’s a simple chamber with no furniture that would explain its purpose. The fireplace is buried beneath the roof. You inspect the walls, made of hundreds of small rocks dressed with a chisel. \n\nThe trash is heavy from the moisture. You push it with your boot, what starts a commotion among gray, disoriented bugs. Removing the rubble would take some effort, but for now it doesn’t look like there’s anything of value left behind. With enough wood, a group of builders could restore this hamlet in just a few days. \n\nYou hear a rustle coming from the backyard. You look through the crumbling wall and notice the movement of a reddish fur. Not a tall creature. "
